parse.title: Letter to Sterling E. Lanier (29 September 1965)

links.*: Letters not published in "The Letters of J.R.R. Tolkien"

wikitext.*:
On [[29 September]] [[1965]], [[J.R.R. Tolkien]] wrote '''[[Letters not published in "The Letters of J.R.R. Tolkien"|a letter]] to Sterling E. Lanier'''.<ref>Oronzo Cilli, ''[[Tolkien's Library: An Annotated Checklist]]''</ref>

*'''Contents:''' Tolkien thanks Lanier for sending him a copy of [[wikipedia:Frank Herbert|Frank Herbert]]'s novel [[wikipedia:Dune (novel)|''Dune'']]. Tolkien writes that he will not have time to read the novel until next time he gets a vacation.
*'''Publication:''' A quotation from the letter was published in ''Tolkien's Library: An Annotated Checklist''.
